  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When transaction is signed, a chat screen re-appears for a moment only to be covered by transaction sent screen a second later. Also, when the chat screen appears, the transaction message is marked as \"Not sent\" which maybe misleading for a user:\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/40482709-f2b3c7f2-5f55-11e8-97a0-caa79b03b38b.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\nA fix for that would be not to show the chat screen at all but immediately show the transaction sent screen. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nChat screen does not appear between sign transaction screen and the transaction sent screen.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nChat screen appears for a moment when transaction is signed. It says that transaction is not set which maybe misleading.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Create 1-1 chat\r\n- Open chat and call /sent to sent transaction\r\n- Sign transaction in Wallet\r\n-> The chat screen appears for a moment\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, May 24\r\n* Operating System: tested only on Android\r\n",
